textAnnotations.description:
NEW ZEALAND UNITED NATIONS SERVICE
REPUBLIC OF KOREA 1950 - 1957
THIS PLAQUE COMMEMORATES NEW ZEALAND'S MILITARY COMMITMENT TO
THE DEFENCE OF THE PRINCIPLES OF THE CHARTER OF THE UNITED NATIONS, IN
PROVIDING ARMED FORCES TO THAT INTERNATIONAL BODY, TO REPEL AGGRESSION
FROM THE NORTH, 25 JUNE 1950.
OVER 1350 ROYAL NZ NAVY PERSONNEL SERVED BETWEEN JULY 1950
4720 NZARMY EMERGENCY FORCE PERSONNEL OF KAYFORCE" BETWEEN AUGUST
JUNE 1956,
SAUGUST 1957 AND 2 ROYAL NZ AIR FORCE PERSONNEL IN 1953.
45 GAVE THEIR LIVES, 81 WERE WOUNDED
1950
SERVICE TO THE UNITED NATIONS IS HEREBY RECORDED.
1950 53
1953 - 54
1954 - 57
NEW ZEALAND KOREA VETERANS ASSOCIATION 2000
LEST WE FORGET
